    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "This hadith from Imam al-Sadiq (AS) describes a scene where Prophet Musa (AS), during his intimate conversation with God, sees a man being honored under the shade of Allah's Throne. When Musa asks about this person's identity, Allah reveals that the man earned this distinction through two qualities: filial piety (birr al-walidayn) and abstaining from gossip (namimah). In early Islamic society, these two traits were considered fundamental to social harmony -- one preserving family bonds, the other preserving community trust.",
        "key_terms": {
          "بَارًّا بِوَالِدَيْهِ": "Good to his parents -- filial piety, a paramount virtue in Islam",
          "النَّمِيمَةِ": "Gossip/tale-bearing -- spreading rumors that sow discord between people",
          "عَرْشِ اللَّهِ": "The Throne of Allah -- the greatest of all created things in Islamic cosmology"
        },
